  "instructions": [
    "Heat the coconut oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the king prawns to the skillet and cook for 1-2 minutes per side, until they are lightly browned and still raw in the center.",
    "Add the scotch bonnet pepper, garlic, and a pinch of salt and pepper to the skillet and cook for another minute.",
    "Stir in the lime juice, fish sauce, and allspice, and cook for a final 30 seconds.",
    "Garnish with chopped cilantro, scallions, and a lime wedge, and serve hot.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning with salt and pepper as needed.",
    "If desired, add a dash of cooking wine for added flavor.",
    "Make sure not to overcook the prawns, as they should still be slightly raw in the center.",
    "If using fish sauce, be sure to stir it in evenly to avoid overpowering the dish.",
    "For a pop of color, garnish with chopped fresh chilies, parsley, or mint, if desired."
